address: Jl. Blabak - Boyolali Tlatar, Krogowanan, Kec. Sawangan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56481, Indonesia
name: Keperluan Penelitian
text:
Candi Lumbung Sengi merupakan salah satu dari tiga candi yang berdekatan di pos sengi. Candi ini sudah dipindahkan dari lokasi aslinya akibat erupsi gunung merapi tahun 2010, dikuatirkan banjir lahar dingin merusak situs candi ini.

Waktu ke tempat ini candi ini dalam keadaan dibongkar untuk dipindahkan lagi.

Tidak ada fasilitas ditempat ini baik parkir maupun toilet dan tidak ada pos penjagaan. Tidak ada tiket masuk ke tempat ini.
textTranslated:
Lumbung Sengi Temple is one of three adjacent temples at the Sengi post. This temple has been moved from its original location due to the eruption of Mount Merapi in 2010, it is feared that cold lava floods will damage this temple site.

When we arrived at this place, the temple was being dismantled to be moved again.

There are no facilities at this place, either parking or toilets, and there is no guard post. There is no entrance ticket to this place.
title: Lumbung Temple

textTranslated: Lumbung temple is a Hindu temple. It used to be located on the river bank. Because the lava was cold it was moved to Tlatar. But now it has been relocated again to Sengi Village, close to Asu Temple and Pendem Temple. However, the relocation is still not complete.

address: Jl. Blabak - Boyolali Tlatar, Krogowanan, Kec. Sawangan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56481, Indonesia
name: galih akademik
text:
Anda pasti kaget ketika mencoba jalur blabak ketep kabupaten magelang, karena candi ini ada di kiri jalan masuk gang sedikit 1 km sebelum obyek wisata ketep pass. Ini bukan Candi Lumbung di kawasan Prambanan. Candi Lumbung Sengi merupakan peninggalan Kerajaan Mataram Kuno yang masuk dalam Kompleks Candi Sengi.

Awalnya, candi ini terletak di Dusun Candipos, Kelurahan Sengi, Kecamatan Dukun, Kabupaten Magelang, satu dusun dengan Candi Asu dan Candi Pendem. Tahun 2011, Candi Lumbung Sengi terpaksa dipindahkan ke Dusun Tlatar, Desa Krogowanan, Kecamatan Sawangan, yang berjarak sekitar 300 meter dari lokasi awal.

Pemindahan dilakukan oleh @bpcbjateng untuk menyelamatkan candi dari terjangan banjir lahar dingin Gunung Merapi. Namun sayang sampai sekarang baru tertata batuan pondasinya saja pak @nadiemmakarim  @infokemendikbud . Terletak di depan kampung dan bersebelahan dengan rumah penduduk. Candi Sengi yang lain segera kita carikan dulu. #literasyikgalih #kilasdokumenter
textTranslated:
You will definitely be surprised when you try the Blabak route to Magelang Regency, because this temple is to the left of the alley entrance a little 1 km before the Ketep Pass tourist attraction. This is not the Lumbung Temple in the Prambanan area. Lumbung Sengi Temple is a relic of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom which is included in the Sengi Temple Complex.

Initially, this temple was located in Candipos Hamlet, Sengi Village, Dukun District, Magelang Regency, in the same hamlet as Asu Temple and Pendem Temple. In 2011, Lumbung Sengi Temple had to be moved to Tlatar Hamlet, Krogowanan Village, Sawangan District, which is about 300 meters from the original location.

The move was carried out by @bpcbjateng to save the temple from the cold lava floods of Mount Merapi. But unfortunately until now only the foundation stones have been laid, Mr @nadiemmakarim @infokemendikbud . Located in front of the village and next to residents' houses. We will immediately look for the other Sengi Temples first. #literaturesyikgalih #documentaryflash

text:
Gondosuli Temple And Inscription : Temanggung レリーフの状態が良いのに、組み上がっていたブロックが全部崩れちゃった様な状態の遺跡でした。
パズルのようだけど、これ頑張って組み上げたら、それこそ美しい遺跡が復元できるんじゃないかな。
時間と金をかけるかどうかだけだね。
駐車場が無かったので目の前の収穫したばかりの籾を地べたにバラマキ乾燥していた地元の農家のオジサンに、少しの間、車を停めさせてもらっていて、遺跡見学から戻ってお礼を言うと、仕切りに私の車(Toyota raise 1000cc ターボ車)をこんな車見たことがないと、中も見せてくれとインパネ周りや外回りを見られていた（笑）　　建屋の横には見たこともない古いトラックが停まっていた🫣
気に入って買った車だから褒められると嬉しいもんだね。
textTranslated:
Gondosuli Temple And Inscription: Temanggung Although the reliefs were in good condition, the ruins looked like all the blocks that had been assembled had collapsed.
It may seem like a puzzle, but if we work hard to put it together, we might be able to restore a beautiful ruin.
It's just a matter of spending time and money.
There was no parking lot, so I parked my car for a while to meet an old man from a local farmer who was drying his freshly harvested paddy on the ground in front of me, and when I returned from my tour of the ruins, I thanked him. I was asked to see the inside of my car (Toyota Raise 1000cc turbo car) and was looking around the instrument panel and outside. There was an old truck parked there🫣
I bought the car because I liked it, so it makes me happy to receive compliments.

address: Jl. Blabak - Boyolali Tlatar, Krogowanan, Kec. Sawangan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56481, Indonesia
name: Achmad Noer Cholis
text:
Candi Lumbung memiliki bentuk bujur sangkar terdiri atas bagian batur, kaki candi & tubuh candi. Pada kaki candi dipahatkan hiasan yang menggambarkan sulur – suluran tumbuhan. Selain itu terdapat makara berkepala ikan yang didalam mulutnya terdapat pahatan burung di pipi tangga. Keunikan kaki candi Lumbung adalah pahatan batu berbentuk kubus yang pada sisi depannya terdapat ukiran seperti bentuk pilar & diukir sulur – suluran yang terletak dibawah makara.
Dan jika kita mengelilingi candi maka akan dijumpai juga relief semacam pohon kalpataru, ada juga relief Gana yaitu makhluk kerdil yang digambarkan sedang menyangga bangunan candi. Hiasan Gana ini menggambarkan tentara atau prajurid pengawal Dewa Siwa & dipimpin oleh Ganesha. Ada juga relief sepasang burung kakak tua di candi ini.
.
Untuk lokasinya sendiri tadinya candi ini  berada di tepi sungai Apu, dikarenakan rawan longsor & ancaman lahar dingin Gunung Merapi akhirnya candi ini dipindah di lokasi sekarang ini oleh BPCB Jawa Tengah.
.
textTranslated:
Lumbung Temple has a square shape consisting of the batur, temple foot & temple body. At the foot of the temple decorations are carved depicting the tendrils of plants. Apart from that, there is a fish-headed makara with a bird carved in its mouth on the cheek of the stairs. What is unique about the foot of Lumbung temple is the cube-shaped stone carving on the front side which has pillar-like carvings & carved tendrils located under the makara.
And if we surround the temple, we will also find reliefs such as kalpataru trees, there are also reliefs of Gana, namely a dwarf creature depicted supporting the temple building. This Gana decoration depicts soldiers or soldiers guarding Lord Shiva & is led by Ganesha. There is also a relief of a pair of parrots in this temple.
.
As for the location itself, this temple was previously on the banks of the Apu river, because it was prone to landslides and the threat of cold lava from Mount Merapi, this temple was finally moved to its current location by the Central Java BPCB.
.
title: Lumbung Temple

text:
Candi Lumbung terletak di Dusun Tlatar, Desa Krogowanan, Kecamatan Sawangan, Kabupaten Magelang. Candi ini berada tepat di tepi Kali Apu, yang mengalir dari Gunung Merapi di lereng sisi barat. Tempat ini dapat dicapai dari jalan raya Yogyakarta-Magelang di pertigaan Blabak (sekitar pabrik kertas) ke arah Ketep. Candi ini terletak berdekatan dengan dua candi lain, yaitu Candi Pendem dan Candi Asu. Ketiga candi sering disebut dengan Candi-candi Sengi.
Tidak jelas apakah nama Lumbung memang merupakan nama candi ini atau nama itu hanya merupakan sebutan masyarakat di sekitarnya karena bentuknya yang mirip lumbung (bangunan tempat penyimpanan padi).
textTranslated:
Lumbung Temple is located in Tlatar Hamlet, Krogowanan Village, Sawangan District, Magelang Regency. This temple is right on the edge of Kali Apu, which flows from Mount Merapi on the western slopes. This place can be reached from the Yogyakarta-Magelang highway at the Blabak T-junction (around the paper factory) towards Ketep. This temple is located close to two other temples, namely Pendem Temple and Asu Temple. The three temples are often called the Sengi Temples.
It is not clear whether the name Lumbung is actually the name of this temple or whether the name is just a nickname for the surrounding community because its shape resembles a granary (a building where rice is stored).
title: Lumbung Temple

name: Dodi Dodi
text:
Candi Lumbung terletak 200 m di sebelah barat daya Candi Asu, dan termasuk dalam wilayah administrasi Desa Tlatar, Kalurahan Kroguwanan, Kecamatan Sawangan, Kabupaten Magelang. Candi Lumbung berada pada ketinggian 750 m di atas permukaan laut dan dikelilingi oleh tebing setinggi 7 m. Candi Lumbung terbuat dari batu andesit dengan struktur batunya masih baik. Arah hadap candi ke barat dengan denah berbentuk bujur sangkar berukuran 8,5 m x 8,5 m, dan tinggi bangunan yang tersisa adalah 6,5 m. Seperti halnya bangunan Candi Asu, bangunan Candi Lumbung juga sudah tidak utuh dinding kaki (plint), bagian atas berupa susunan pelipit datar.

Hiasan yang berada di bagian kaki candi sebelah timur dan selatan berupa tumbuhan sulur gelung yang dipahatkan pada bidang relief Bagian tubuh candi yang mengalami kerusakan adalah bagian luar dinding candi, karena sebagian besar batu penyusun tubuh candi paling luar tersebut sudah hilang. Kondisi tubuh candi sebagian besar sudah rusak, sedangkan bagian yang masih lengkap adalah bagian tubuh candi bawah, sementara itu bagian tubuh candi tengah dan atas sudah tidak diketahui bentuknya lagi. Hiasan di tubuh candi berupa relung dengan hiasan pola bunga berbingkai belah ketupat dan hiasan pola simbar. Ukuran lebar relung bagian luar 81 cm dan lebar relung bagian dalam 5 1 cm, dengan kedalaman 42 cm, tetapi tingginya tidak diketahui karena sudah rusak. Bagian atap candi sudah tidak diketahui bentuk aslinya, karena tidak ada sama sekali batu yang tersusun pada posisinya. Batu penyusun atap candi ditemukan dalam keadaan bercampur dengan batu lainnya di halaman candi. Hiasan yang terdapat di Candi Lumbung lebih banyak dari pada di Candi Asu, seperti adanya hiasan sulur gelung yang keluar dari ketiak gana, sulur gelung yang keluar dari jambangan, dan pahatan burung nuri di kanan kiri sulur. Terdapatjuga hiasan tumpal yang dijumpai di pelipit atas kaki candi, sedangkan di bagian dinding luar pipi tangga yang berbentuk makara terdapat hiasan sulur gelung yang keluar dari mahluk bercakar. Ujung makara tersebut berbentuk kepala ikan dan di dalamnya terdapat hiasan burung. Hiasan antefik yang biasanya terletak di bagian atap candi, tetapi di Candi Lumbung hiasan antefik terdapat di bagian tubuh bagian bawah yang berjumlah empat pada sisi selatan dan timur, serta dua pada sisi barat. Seperti halnya Candi Asu, kemungkinan kerusakan Candi Lumbung juga disebabkan oleh faktor alam, karena kedekatan dengan Gunung Merapi. Mungkin juga disebabkan oleh faktor manusia yang memanfaatkan batu-batu candi untuk membangun rumah atau keperluan lainnya..
(Renville Siagian, Candi Sebagai Warisan Seni Budaya Indonesia, Yayasan Cempaka Kencana, Yogyakarta, 2002, hal. 51-52)
textTranslated:
Lumbung Temple is located 200 m southwest of Asu Temple, and is included in the administrative area of ​​Tlatar Village, Kroguwanan Village, Sawangan District, Magelang Regency. Lumbung Temple is at an altitude of 750 m above sea level and is surrounded by cliffs as high as 7 m. Lumbung Temple is made of andesite stone and the stone structure is still good. The temple faces west with a square plan measuring 8.5 m x 8.5 m, and the height of the remaining building is 6.5 m. Like the Asu Temple building, the Lumbung Temple building also has no intact foot walls (plints), the top part is a flat seam structure.

The decorations at the foot of the temple to the east and south are in the form of coiled vine plants carved into the relief area. The part of the temple body that was damaged was the outer part of the temple wall, because most of the stones that made up the outermost body of the temple had been lost. The condition of the temple body is mostly damaged, while the part that is still complete is the lower temple body, while the shape of the middle and upper temple bodies is no longer known. The decoration on the body of the temple is in the form of a niche decorated with floral patterns framed by rhombuses and decorative simbar patterns. The width of the outer niche is 81 cm and the width of the inner niche is 5 1 cm, with a depth of 42 cm, but the height is unknown because it is damaged. The original shape of the roof of the temple is unknown, because there are no stones at all arranged in its position. The stones that make up the roof of the temple were found mixed with other stones in the temple yard. There are more decorations in Lumbung Temple than in Asu Temple, such as coiled tendrils coming out of the gana's armpits, coiled tendrils coming out of the vase, and parrot carvings on either side of the tendrils. There are also tumpal decorations found on the top seam of the foot of the temple, while on the outer wall of the makara-shaped stairs there are coiled tendril decorations coming out of clawed creatures. The tip of the makara is in the shape of a fish head and inside is a bird decoration. The antefic decorations are usually located on the roof of the temple, but in Lumbung Temple the antefic decorations are found on the lower body, totaling four on the south and east sides, and two on the west side. Like Asu Temple, it is possible that damage to Lumbung Temple was also caused by natural factors, due to its proximity to Mount Merapi. It may also be caused by human factors using temple stones to build houses or other purposes.
(Renville Siagian, Temples as Indonesian Cultural Arts Heritage, Cempaka Kencana Foundation, Yogyakarta, 2002, pp. 51-52)
title: Lumbung Temple

address: 978W+8P7, Canggal, Kadiluwih, Salam, Area Kebun, Kadiluwih, Kec. Salam, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56484, Indonesia
name: Khilsa Azkania
text:
Gunung Wukir temple, or Canggal temple, or also known as Shivalinga is a Shivaite Hindu temple dated from early 8th century, located in Canggal hamlet, Kadiluwih village, Salam subdistrict, Magelang Regency, Central Java, Indonesia.

The temple dates to the year 732, making it the first structure attributed to the ancient Mataram kingdom, which ruled Central Java from 732 to around the middle of the tenth century.

Because of its relatively remote location, the temple site rarely appears on the itineraries of foreign tourists. But it possesses some historical importance owed to its links with the formation of the Central Javanese Mataram kingdom.

The temple is located on Wukir hill, which the locals refer to as Gunung Wukir ("Mount Wukir", or "carved hill" in Javanese), on the western slopes of Mount Merapi volcano. The hill is located approximately 4 kilometres southeast from the town of Muntilan. Gunung Wukir temple can be reached by following the direction to the Ngluwar subdistrict by turning west from the Semen intersection, on Yogyakarta-Magelang main road. The Kadiluwih hamlet in Canggal, is connected to the Ngluwar road by a small walking trail that leads up to the hill plateau, approximately 300 meters above sea level.

This temple is the oldest surviving temple in Southern Central Java, connected to the Canggal inscription discovered within the temple ruins in 1879.

According to the inscription, the temple was founded during the reign of King Sanjaya from the Mataram Kingdom, in 654 Saka (732 CE).

This inscription contains a lot of information related to Medang Kingdom or Hindu Mataram. Based on this inscription, Gunung Wukir temple might originally called Shivalinga or Kunjarakunja.

Source : Wikipedia

text:
Plang petunjuk yang tidak jelas akan menjadi kendala pertama untuk menuju tempat ini, namun titik di Maps sudah tepat. Candi ini terletak di atas bukit, dimana terdapat kampung kecil di bawahnya. Disarankan untuk bertanya ke warga tentang jalan naik yang benar.

Ada dua jalan setapak yang menuju ke Candi. Satu jalur bisa dilalui oleh motor namun tidak disarankan apabila anda adalah tamu, karena jalannya yang sangat curam dan berkelok tanpa ada pembatas jalan sehingga licin sedikit berisiko jatuh ke jurang. Jalur satunya lagi melalui kebun bambu dengan beberapa anak tangga. Pastikan bawa air minum karena akan cukup melelahkan dan di sekitaran Candi tidak terdapat tempat berteduh.

Kompleks Candi sangat terawat. Penjaganya juga sangat sopan. Karena tidak ada biaya masuk, pastikan anda tetap meminta izin ke penjaga dan mengisi buku tamu.
textTranslated:
Unclear signage will be the first obstacle to getting to this place, but the point on Maps is correct. This temple is located on a hill, where there is a small village below. It is recommended to ask residents about the correct way up.

There are two paths leading to the temple. One route can be passed by motorbike but it is not recommended if you are a guest, because the road is very steep and winding without any road dividers so it is slippery and there is a risk of falling into a ravine. The other route goes through a bamboo garden with several stairs. Make sure to bring drinking water because it will be quite tiring and there are no shelters around the temple.

The temple complex is very well maintained. The guards are also very polite. Because there is no entrance fee, make sure you still ask permission from the guard and fill in the guest book.
title: Gunung Wukir Temple

name: Keperluan Penelitian
text:
Candi Gunung Wukir merupakan candi yang ada di atas bukit. Akses ke tempat ini cukup sulit karena papan penunjuk yang tidak jelas serta belum adanya jalan yang memadai untuk orang-orang berkunjung dengan nyaman.

Hal yang perlu diperhatikan :

1. Sampai ke tempat ini sudah sesuai titik yang ditunjukkan google maps, patokannya anda akan menemukan Mushola.

2. Untuk ke atas candi, dari Mushola anda terus ke arah kiri sejauh 50 meter, atau lebih mudah tanyakan ke penduduk sekitar, mereka akan menunjukkan jalan setapak disamping rumah warga untuk menuju ke dalam hutan bambu, anda akan melalui jembatan beton dan terus ke arah rimbunan pohon bambu.

3. Pendakian tidak jauh hanya memakan 10-15 menit, namun tidak adanya petunjuk jalan membuat anda harus memperhatikan jalan setapak yang menuju keatas, pada musim kemarau jalan ini tampak jelas namun pada saat musim penghujan jalanan sangat becek.

4. Perhatikan jam kunjungan. Di atas ada petugas yang menjaga, namun pagar candi akan ditutup diluar jam kunjung.

Tidak ada tiket masuk ke tempat ini hanya melapor ke petugas dan mengisi buku tamu. Ada toilet di pos penjaga.

Bagi orang-orang yang mengunjungi tempat ini biasanya didominasi pencinta sejarah, siswa-mahasiswa, atau orang yang handak menggunakan candi sebagai tempat ritual keagamaan. Suasana di atas cukup sejuk dan tenang.

Jangan lupa bawa air minum. Dan disarankan tidak bepergian sendiri demi menghindari tersesat. Sinyal internet diatas cukup baik.
textTranslated:
Gunung Wukir Temple is a temple on a hill. Access to this place is quite difficult because the signage is not clear and there are no adequate roads for people to visit comfortably.

Things to note :

1. Arriving at this place is at the point shown on Google Maps, the benchmark is that you will find the prayer room.

2. To go to the top of the temple, from the prayer room you continue to the left for 50 meters, or it's easier to ask the local residents, they will show you a path next to the residents' houses to go into the bamboo forest, you will go through a concrete bridge and continue towards grove of bamboo trees.

3. The climb is not far, it only takes 10-15 minutes, but there are no road signs so you have to pay attention to the path that leads up, in the dry season this road is clear, but during the rainy season the road is very muddy.

4. Pay attention to visiting hours. There are officers on guard at the top, but the temple fence will be closed outside visiting hours.

There is no entrance ticket to this place, just report to the officer and fill in the guest book. There is a toilet at the guard post.

People who visit this place are usually dominated by history lovers, students, or people who want to use the temple as a place for religious rituals. The atmosphere above is quite cool and calm.

Don't forget to bring drinking water. And it is recommended not to travel alone to avoid getting lost. The internet signal above is quite good.

text:
Candi Losari merupakan candi Hindu yang tertimbun sedalam 5 meter. Berada di tengah area kebun salak, candi ini menyisakan sebuah candi induk dan tiga candi perwara dan sekelilingnya terdapat sisa-sisa reruntuhan batu candi. Di reruntuhan candi juga masih ada ditemukan arca yang hanya menyisakan bagian kaki.

Lokasi candi kurang lebih 50 meter dari jalan utama. Untuk masuk ke tempat ini tidak ada tiket masuk hanya melapor ke petugas untuk mengisi buku tamu. Candi ini bukan candi yang ramai dikunjungi. Suasana disekitarnya sangat tenang. Ada toilet di pos penjagaan.

Candi ini selain untuk tujuan edukasi sejarah, juga bisa digunakan untuk tujuan edukasi geologi, karena candi ini tertimbun endapan erupsi gunung api.

Candi Losari buka pukul 08:00 - 16:00
textTranslated:
Losari Temple is a Hindu temple buried 5 meters deep. Located in the middle of the salak garden area, this temple contains a main temple and three ancillary temples and around it are the remains of stone temple ruins. In the ruins of the temple, statues were still found that only left the legs.

The location of the temple is approximately 50 meters from the main road. There is no entrance ticket to enter this place, just report to the officer to fill in the guest book. This temple is not a temple that is visited by many people. The atmosphere around is very calm. There is a toilet at the guard post.

Apart from being used for historical educational purposes, this temple can also be used for geological educational purposes, because this temple is covered in sediment from volcanic eruptions.

Losari Temple is open 08:00 - 16:00

text:
Candi Losari ditemukan di tengah kebun salak ketika Badri, pemiliknya, menggali parit pada tanggal 11 Mei 2004. Di galian tersebut ternyata terdapat banyak batu candi. Badri, seorang guru SMP Negeri 12 di Kota Magelang, membawa pulang batu-batu tersebut dan menyusun lagi di halaman rumahnya. Penemuan ini kemudian ditindaklanjuti dengan ekskavasi arkeologis dan rekonstruksi oleh pemerintah melalui Balai Pelestarian Peninggalan Purbakala Jawa Tengah dan Balai Arkeologi Yogyakarta.
Untuk mengunjungi candi losari cukup mengisi buku tamu.
Setelah pandemi belum ada aktifitas kembali.
textTranslated:
Losari Temple was discovered in the middle of a salak plantation when Badri, the owner, dug a trench on May 11 2004. In the excavation, it turned out that there were many temple stones. Badri, a teacher at SMP Negeri 12 in Magelang City, took the stones home and arranged them again in his yard. This discovery was then followed up with archaeological excavations and reconstruction by the government through the Central Java Archaeological Heritage Conservation Center and the Yogyakarta Archaeological Center.
To visit Losari temple, just fill in the guest book.
After the pandemic there has been no return to activity.

text:
Candi Pendem Sengi merupakan salah satu dari tiga candi yang berdekatan di pos sengi. Di dekatnya ada Candi Asu Sengi dan Candi Lumbung Sengi.

Kemungkinan besar merupakan candi Hindu, hanya kaki candi dan setengah badan candi saja yang utuh. Mirip keadaannya dengan Candi Asu.

Candi ini cukup sulit diakses karena berada di antara perkebunan warga. Jarak dari candi Asu kurang lebih 400 meter berjalan kaki. Waktu ke tempat ini dalam keadaan tutup waktu itu pukul 14:30, sepertinya Candi Pendem dan Candi Asu yang di dekatnya tutup pukul 14:00. Bila ke candi ini diatas jam itu candi masih bisa dikunjungi hanya tidak bisa masuk ke dalam karena pintu pagar terkunci. Bila ke tempat ini jangan lupa bertanya ke masyarakat sekitar supaya tidak tersesat diperkebunan warga karna tidak ada jalan yang jelas menuju candi ini hanya melalui pemantang setapak pemisah kebun.

Tidak ada fasilitas parkir atau toilet. Tidak ada tiket masuk ke tempat ini. Sepertinya cukup melapor ke petugasnya kalau ingin masuk ke candi.
textTranslated:
Pendem Sengi Temple is one of three adjacent temples at the Sengi post. Nearby are Asu Sengi Temple and Lumbung Sengi Temple.

Most likely a Hindu temple, only the foot of the temple and half of the body of the temple are intact. The situation is similar to Asu Temple.

This temple is quite difficult to access because it is located between local plantations. The distance from Asu temple is approximately 400 meters on foot. When this place closed, it was at 14:30, it seems that Pendem Temple and the nearby Asu Temple closed at 14:00. If you go to this temple after that time, you can still visit the temple, but you can't go inside because the gate is locked. If you go to this place, don't forget to ask the local people so you don't get lost in people's plantations because there is no clear road to this temple, only through the footpath separating the gardens.

There are no parking or toilet facilities. There is no entrance ticket to this place. It seems that you just need to report to the staff if you want to enter the temple.
title: Candi Pendem Sengi

address: F9F2+PQ8, Desa Candi,, Ngampel, Sengi, Kec. Dukun, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56482, Indonesia
name: ecchi epen
text:
Lokasi Candi Pendhem berdekatan dengan Candi Asu. Namun kita harus berjalan kaki melewati jalan setapak dan pematang sawah. Sebaiknya titipkam kendaraan Anda di sekolah dasar di depan Candi Asu.

Dari plang candi Pendhem kita cukup menyusuri jalan setapak. Sekitar 50 m, ada percabangan ke kanan adalah ke rumah-rumah warga. Ke kiri adalah ke Candi Pendhem.

Karena terletak di tengah-tengah persawahan, ada baiknya kita memohon izin ke warga setempat. Kita akan menyusuri pematang sawah hingga Candi Pendhem. Sebaiknya pergilah kesana ketika hari cerah agar jalan tidak becek/jeblok.
textTranslated:
The location of Pendhem Temple is close to Asu Temple. However, we have to walk through paths and rice fields. It's best to leave your vehicle at the elementary school in front of Asu Temple.

From the Pendhem temple sign, we just walk along the path. About 50 m, there is a branch to the right that leads to people's houses. To the left is Pendhem Temple.

Because it is located in the middle of rice fields, it is a good idea to ask local residents for permission. We will walk along the rice fields to Pendhem Temple. It's best to go there on a sunny day so that the road isn't muddy/blocked.
title: Candi Pendem Sengi

address: F9F2+PQ8, Desa Candi,, Ngampel, Sengi, Kec. Dukun, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56482, Indonesia
name: Ibu Djang
text: Akses ke candi nya menurut saya sangat susah sekali, seperti candi rahasia, harus cari jalan sendiri. Candi nya menurut saya terawat, terdapat candi Asu dan Candi Lumbung di dekat candi Pendem. Di salah satu batu nya terdapat ukiran2 yang belum selesai, dan ada yang menyerupai media untuk bermain dakon. Jika cuaca sedang bagus kita bisa menikmati pemandangan gunung Merapi dan Merbabu dari candi ini. Untuk foto pun sangat bagus. Semoga selalu terawat dan lestari. Rahayu.
textTranslated: In my opinion, access to the temple is very difficult, like a secret temple, you have to find your own way. In my opinion, the temples are well maintained, there are Asu temple and Lumbung temple near Pendem temple. On one of the stones there are unfinished carvings, and there is something that resembles a medium for playing dakon. If the weather is good we can enjoy views of Mount Merapi and Merbabu from this temple. It's also very good for photos. Hopefully it will always be maintained and sustainable. Rahayu.
title: Candi Pendem Sengi

address: F9F2+PQ8, Desa Candi,, Ngampel, Sengi, Kec. Dukun, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56482, Indonesia
name: Ephin N
text: Candi Pendem Muntilan Magelang pada awalnya ditemukan oleh petani yang mencangkul lahan, kemudian digali oleh seorang Belanda bernama de Plink. Penggaliannya tidak ia lakukan seorang diri namun juga bersama dengan masyarakat. candi ini berada di Dusun Sengi, Kabupaten Magelang, Kecamatan Dukun, Jawa Tengah. Candi Pendem ini merupakan candi Hindu yang berlokasi tidak jauh dari candi Triloginya yakni Candi Lumbung dan Candi Asu. Ketiga candi tersebut juga dikenal dengan sebuatan candi-candi Sengi.
textTranslated: Pendem Muntilan Magelang Temple was originally discovered by farmers who were hoeing the land, then excavated by a Dutchman named de Plink. He did not carry out his excavations alone but also together with the community. This temple is located in Sengi Hamlet, Magelang Regency, Dukun District, Central Java. Pendem Temple is a Hindu temple which is located not far from the Trilogy temples, namely Lumbung Temple and Asu Temple. These three temples are also known as the Sengi temples.
title: Candi Pendem Sengi

text:
Salah satu candi kecil yang ada di sekitaran Magelang. Tidak sulit menemukan candi ini karena berada tidak jauh dari jalan ketep pass. Karena kecil mungkin candi ini tidak ditarik biaya masuk kali ya, hehehe
Sekeliling candi tidak dilengkapi dengan pagar pengaman seperti di candi asu. Khawatir aja kalau sampai ada yang ambil batu batu relief nya.
Untuk informasi lebih lengkap bisa dibaca di papan informasi yang ada di dekat candi
textTranslated:
One of the small temples around Magelang. It is not difficult to find this temple because it is not far from the Ketep Pass road. Because this temple is small, perhaps there is no entrance fee, hehehe
There is no safety fence around the temple like at Asu Temple. Just worry if someone takes the relief stones.
For more complete information, you can read the information board near the temple

textTranslated:
Mount Wukir Temple, a historical heritage that should be preserved.
The place is far from a hill, and in my opinion it is very quiet. The road to the location is also poorly maintained.
The road to the temple is on the north side, precisely from the village of Carikan Kadiluwih Salam, and there are stairs going up.
For those who like a challenge, you can go up from the south side, specifically from Grogolan or Jambon hamlet (sorry if you said the name of the hamlet wrongly).
From the south side the road is still a footpath and has to pass through several cemeteries, including a cemetery which many people call an ancient cemetery. The location of the cemetery is on the south side of the temple. To pass through this route, please be careful with the large number of twigs or leaf litter covering the road.
I myself prefer to go up from the south side, and have repeatedly climbed to Mount Wukir temple from the south side. Have a good adventure at Mount Wukir temple

address: 978W+8P7, Canggal, Kadiluwih, Salam, Area Kebun, Kadiluwih, Kec. Salam, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56484, Indonesia
name: Dodi Dodi
text:
Gunung Wukir adalah sebuah nama bukit yang terkenal dalam sejarah kuno Indonesia. Di dekat bukit Wukir inilah ditemukan prasasti tertua di Jawa tengah, yaitu Prasasti Canggal, yang berangka tahun 732 M. Prasasti itu berasal dari masa pemerintahan Raja Sanjaya, yakni salah satu raja dari Dinasti Sailendra yang beraliran agama Hindu. Pada masa pemerintahan Raja Sanjaya, banyak dihasilkan bangunan berupa candi, salah satunya adalah candi yang berada di atas puncak bukit datar yang bernama Candi Gunung Wukir. Keberadaan dari candi ini dihubungkan dengan temuan Prasasti Canggal, sehingga diperkirakan oleh para ahli sejarah bahwa Candi Gunune Wukir termasuk candi tertua di Jawa Tengah.

Kompleks percandian Gunung Wukir adalah kelompok bangunan candi yang terdiri atas satu candi induk dan di depannya ada tiga buah candi perwara. Kelompok candi berada pada suatu halaman candi yang dikelilingi oleh pagar tembok yang terbuat dari batu bata. Pada keempat sudut dan pertengahan tiap-tiap sisi terdapat lingga-lingga patok (tiang-tiang batu kecil), dan periuk-periuk kecil dari tanah, yang berfungsi sama dengan candi-candi sudut dan kelir pada kompleks percandian Prambanan. Candi induk saat ini hanya tinggal bagian kaki dan batur candi, yang di atasnya terdapat sebuah lapik besar, yang semula terpelosok ke dalam sumuran candi, tetapi sekarang telah diletakkan kembali ke tempat asalnya. Pintu masuk candi terletak di sebelah timur, berupa sebuah pintu yang berhiaskan kala makara. Ambang atasnya telah ditemukan di sebuah desa terdekat, dan telah dipasang kembali. Pada tahun 1937 M - 1939 M, dilakukan penggalian di halaman candi, dan berhasil menemukan sebuah makara yang indah. Di hadapan dengan pintu masuk candi induk terletak tiga buah candi perwara yang berjajar dari utara ke selatan. Pola percandian, yaitu candi induk yang dihadapkan dengan tiga candi perwara, merupakan pola umum yang dijumpai pada candi-candi di Jawa Tengah. Candi perwara yang paling utara sebagian besar telah dibangun kembali pada tahun 1938 - 1939, tetapi candi yang berdiri tegak jumlahnya sedikit. Bangunan candi perwara hanya tinggal bagian kaki, batur dan sebuah pagar langkan di atasnya, serta sebuah pintu gerbang yang sederhana. Diperkirakan bagian atas candi perwara tersebut berkonstruksi kayu, dan hal ini didukung oleh data lubang-lubang segi empat pada batu-batu lantai, yang kemungkinan dipakai untuk menegakkan tiang- tiang kayu. Pada halaman candi ditemukan sejumlah batu-batu candi dan beberapa arca, yang kemungkinan sebagian berasal dari tempat lain. Sekitar 150 m di sebelah selatan kelompok candi, ditemukan sebuah pondasi candi kecil dengan sebuah sumuran. Menurut keterangan penduduk setempat, pada tahun 1879 di lokasi tersebut telah ditemukan prasasti berangka tahun 732 M, dan diberi nama Prasasti Canggal, sesuai dengan nama desa penemuannya yang terletak di kaki bukit. Prasasti itu menceritakan tentang Raja Sanjaya yang telah mendirikan sebuah punden lingga. Dugaan ini dikuatkan dengan adanya lapik besar di candi induk dalam kelompok besar tadi, dan di duga punden lingga yang dimaksud di dalam Prasasti Canggal adalah lingga di dalam candi induk Gunung Wukir. (Renville Siagian, Candi Sebagai Warisan Seni Budaya Indonesia, Yayasan Cempaka Kencana, Yogyakarta, 2002)
textTranslated:
Mount Wukir is the name of a famous hill in ancient Indonesian history. It was near Wukir Hill that the oldest inscription was found in Central Java, namely the Canggal Inscription, which is dated to 732 AD. This inscription comes from the reign of King Sanjaya, who was one of the kings of the Hindu Sailendra Dynasty. During the reign of King Sanjaya, many temple buildings were produced, one of which was a temple located on a flat hilltop called Gunung Wukir Temple. The existence of this temple is linked to the discovery of the Canggal Inscription, so it is estimated by historians that Gunune Wukir Temple is one of the oldest temples in Central Java.

The Gunung Wukir temple complex is a group of temple buildings consisting of one main temple and in front of it there are three ancillary temples. The temple group is located in a temple courtyard surrounded by a brick fence. At the four corners and in the middle of each side there are phallus stakes (small stone pillars) and small earthen pots, which function in the same way as the corner temples and kelir in the Prambanan temple complex. Currently, only the base and foot of the temple remain, on top of which there is a large pedestal, which was originally hidden in the temple well, but has now been placed back in its original place. The entrance to the temple is located to the east, in the form of a door decorated with kala makara. The upper lintel had been found in a nearby village, and had been reinstalled. In 1937 AD - 1939 AD, excavations were carried out in the temple grounds, and they managed to find a beautiful makara. In front of the main temple entrance there are three ancillary temples lined up from north to south. The enshrinement pattern, namely the main temple facing three ancillary temples, is a common pattern found in temples in Central Java. The northernmost perwara temple was mostly rebuilt in 1938 - 1939, but there are only a few temples standing upright. The building of the Perwara temple only has the foot, the stone and a balustrade above it, as well as a simple gate. It is estimated that the top of the perwara temple was of wooden construction, and this is supported by data on rectangular holes in the floor stones, which were probably used to erect wooden pillars. In the temple yard, a number of temple stones and several statues were found, some of which may have come from other places. About 150 m to the south of the temple group, a small temple foundation was found with a well. According to information from local residents, in 1879 an inscription dated 732 AD was found at this location, and it was named the Canggal Inscription, after the name of the village where it was discovered which is located at the foot of the hill. The inscription tells about King Sanjaya who had erected a punden phallus. This suspicion is strengthened by the presence of a large pedestal in the main temple in this large group, and it is suspected that the punden phallus referred to in the Canggal Inscription is the phallus in the main temple of Gunung Wukir. (Renville Siagian, Temples as Indonesian Cultural Arts Heritage, Cempaka Kencana Foundation, Yogyakarta, 2002)
